<subSubSection id="C3776556EEB33BD1FC9AFF3FFEBBF835" lastPageId="484" lastPageNumber="485" pageId="482" pageNumber="483" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB33BD7FC9AFF3FFB7EFD26" blockId="482.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB33BD7FC9AFF3FFBAFFECA" bold="true" box="[863,1130,241,267]" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Descriptionoffemale</emphasis>
. Body (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FB15FF3FFA8EFECA" box="[1232,1355,241,267]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320A</figureCitation>
) curved ventrally, 1.07 mmlong. Prosome 836 μmlong, consisting of cephalosome and distinctly 4-segmented metasome. Dorsal cephalic shield with prominent paired horn-like process (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FC49FEB7FC3AFE52" box="[908,1023,377,403]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320D</figureCitation>
) posterolaterally, each bearing 2 small tuberclesdistally. Fourthpedigeroussomiteslightlylonger than anterior part of metasome. Free urosome (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FAF7FE73FA61FE16" box="[1330,1444,445,471]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320B</figureCitation>
) 5-segmented. Anal somite and caudal rami ornamented with numerous setules on all surfaces. Caudal rami divergent, evenly tapering; ramus (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FB7EFDEDFAEAFDFC" box="[1211,1327,547,573]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320C</figureCitation>
) about 3.1 times longer than wide (89×29 μm) and 1.6 times longer than anal somite: armed with 6 setae (outer lateral, dorsal, and 4 distal); outer lateral and dorsal setae positioned at 43 and 51% of ramus length; all caudal setae naked and shorter than width of ramus at base.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB33BD7FC9AFD3EFAA1FB41" blockId="482.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">
Rostrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FC11FD21FB8FFCC8" box="[980,1098,751,777]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320E</figureCitation>
) 82×50 μm, bearing scattered setules; lateral margins parallel proximally, and evenly tapering over distal four-fifths. Antennule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FAE8FCFDFA61FC8C" box="[1325,1444,819,845]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320F</figureCitation>
) 110 μmlong, 7-segmented; armatureformula 2, 13, 4, 3+aesthetasc, 2, 2+aesthetasc, and 12+aesthetasc; setae moderately long, all naked. Antenna (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FAEEFC57FA66FC72" box="[1323,1443,921,947]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320G</figureCitation>
) consistingof coxa, basis, and 2-segmented endopod; proximal 3 segments unarmed; endopodal segments with few setules; compound distal endopodal segment about 2.9 timeslongerthan wide (40×14 μm): armedwith 6 smallsetae (grouped as 1, 2, and 3) plusterminal claw, more than half length of distal endopodal segment.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB33BD7FC9AFB49FAE9F900" blockId="482.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">
Labrum (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FC12FB49FB99FB60" box="[983,1116,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320H</figureCitation>
) simple, denselysetulose posteriorly. Mandible (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FBE8FB67FB5DFB02" box="[1069,1176,1193,1219]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320I</figureCitation>
) with 5 teethand 1 seta on coxal gnathobase; basis with 1 seta on medial margin: exopod with 5 setae (innermost and outermost subequal in length and both about 0.6 times as long as 3 larger middle setae): endopod 2-segmented; first segment with 1 broad setaonmedial margin; secondwith 4 setae, outerdistalseta longest (1.5 timeslongerthan mediodistalseta). Maxillule (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FCF7FA59FC5EFA73" box="[818,923,1431,1458]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320J</figureCitation>
) lacking coxal endite and armed as usual: 9 seta on arthrite, 1 on epipodite, 1 on basis, 4 on exopod, and 3 on endopod. Maxilla (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FBEDFA15FB5AFA37" box="[1064,1183,1499,1526]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 320K</figureCitation>
) 4-segmented; syncoxa with 4, 2, and 3 setae (including minute proximal seta) on first to third endites, respectively; basis with smooth clawplus 1 seta; endopod with 1 and 3 setaeon first and second segments, respectively. Maxilliped (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FAEFF9ADFA61F9BF" box="[1322,1444,1635,1662]" captionStart="FIGURE 321" captionStartId="484.[136,239,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[166,1398,203,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-20@484.[136,1451,182,1456]" captionTargetPageId="484" captionText="FIGURE 321. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591947/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 321A</figureCitation>
) unsegmented, tapering distally, armed with 6 setae and ornamented with spinules along outer margin,
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB33BD7FC9AF904FC10F813" blockId="482.[810,1452,173,2002]" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">
Legs 1–4 with 3-segmented rami (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FAC1F907FAAEF925" box="[1284,1387,1737,1764]" captionStart="FIGURE 321" captionStartId="484.[136,239,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[166,1398,203,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-20@484.[136,1451,182,1456]" captionTargetPageId="484" captionText="FIGURE 321. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591947/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 321</figureCitation>
B-D); inner seta absent on coxa of all legs. Leg 1 lacking inner distal spine on basis. First endopodal segment of leg 1 broad. Legs 2 and 3 with same armature formula. All setae on legs 2–4 naked and bluntly tipped. Distal seta on third endopodal segment short in left leg 4 (as in 
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB33BD7FABAF8BAFCACF871" captionStart="FIGURE 321" captionStartId="484.[136,239,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[166,1398,203,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-20@484.[136,1451,182,1456]" captionTargetPageId="484" captionText="FIGURE 321. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591947/files/figure.png" pageId="482" pageNumber="483">Fig. 321D</figureCitation>
) but longer in right leg 4. Armature formula for legs 1–4 as follows:
</paragraph>
<caption id="DF126655EEB23BD6FF4DF8BDFC09F813" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="483" pageNumber="484" startId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" targetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" targetPageId="483">
