</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB53BD1FF78F8C0FF24F813" blockId="484.[136,778,1805,2070]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
Leg 5 (
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB53BD1FEE5F8C0FE6DF8E9" box="[288,424,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 320" captionStartId="483.[136,245,1907,1933]" captionTargetBox="[243,1338,225,1844]" captionTargetId="figure-17@483.[209,1379,185,1870]" captionTargetPageId="483" captionText="FIGURE 320. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, habitus, left; B, leg 5 and urosome, ventral; C, left caudal ramus, dorsal; D, posterolateral process of cephalic shield; E, rostrum; F, antennule; G, antenna; H, labrum; I, mandible; J, maxillule; K, maxilla. Scale bars: A, 0.1 mm; B, 0.05 mm; C–K, 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591945" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591945/files/figure.png" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">Figs. 320B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="13562A58EEB53BD1FE78F8C0FE3CF8E9" box="[445,505,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 321" captionStartId="484.[136,239,1499,1525]" captionTargetBox="[166,1398,203,1426]" captionTargetId="figure-20@484.[136,1451,182,1456]" captionTargetPageId="484" captionText="FIGURE 321. Doroixys fijiensis sp. nov., female. A, maxilliped; B, leg 1; C, leg 2; D, leg 4; E, leg 5. Scale bars: 0.02 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4591947" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4591947/files/figure.png" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">321E</figureCitation>
) represented by blunt posteroventral lobe on somite tipped with protopodal seta and tapering inner process (representing exopod) bearing 1 small seta and 1 tubercle on subdistal outer margin, ornamented with several setules scattered on ventral surface.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB53BD1FF78F814FEBBF835" blockId="484.[136,778,1805,2070]" box="[189,382,2010,2036]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FF78F814FF3FF835" bold="true" box="[189,250,2010,2036]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">Male</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3776556EEB53BD0FF78F832FEA0FEB0" lastPageId="485" lastPageNumber="486" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BD236DDEEB53BD0FF78F832FEA0FEB0" blockId="484.[136,778,1805,2070]" lastBlockId="485.[136,778,173,369]" lastPageId="485" lastPageNumber="486" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FF78F832FEEFF7D7" bold="true" box="[189,298,2044,2070]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">Remarks</emphasis>
. The lack of an inner distal spine on the basis of leg 1 is shared between only three species, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FA55F9AAFC44F961" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fijiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FA55F9AAFC44F961" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC4FF948FC23F961" bold="true" box="[906,998,1670,1696]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FC4FF948FC23F961" box="[906,998,1670,1696]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FC33F948FB45F95E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1014,1152,1669,1696]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gryphina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC33F948FBCFF95E" box="[1014,1034,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FBDEF94BFB45F95E" box="[1051,1152,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">gryphina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FB4CF948FB20F961" bold="true" box="[1161,1253,1670,1696]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FB4CF948FB20F961" box="[1161,1253,1670,1696]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FAE5F948FA69F95E" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1312,1452,1669,1696]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodulosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FAE5F948FAF1F95E" box="[1312,1332,1670,1695]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FA80F94BFA69F95E" box="[1349,1452,1669,1695]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">nodulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FCEFF966FC42F903" bold="true" box="[810,903,1704,1730]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FCEFF966FC42F903" box="[810,903,1704,1730]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
Both 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FC17F966FB8AF903" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[978,1103,1704,1730]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fijiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC17F966FB8AF903" box="[978,1103,1704,1730]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FB9FF966FB72F903" bold="true" box="[1114,1207,1704,1730]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FB9FF966FB72F903" box="[1114,1207,1704,1730]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FB31F966FABAF900" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1268,1407,1703,1730]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gryphina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FB31F966FACDF900" box="[1268,1288,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FADFF969FABAF900" box="[1306,1407,1703,1729]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">gryphina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FA4FF966FC9EF925" bold="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FA4FF966FC9EF925" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
have caudal rami with a length/width ratio of about 3.0 or 3.1:1, a setulose anal somite and caudal rami, and distinctly 3-segmented endopods inlegs 2 and 3. In contrast, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FC68F8FEFBF3F88B" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[941,1078,1840,1866]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nodulosa" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC68F8FEFC04F888" box="[941,961,1840,1865]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC0AF8FEFBF3F88B" box="[975,1078,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">nodulosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FBF8F8FEFB53F88B" bold="true" box="[1085,1174,1840,1866]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FBF8F8FEFB53F88B" box="[1085,1174,1840,1866]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the caudal rami are only 2.0 timeslongerthan wide, theanal somiteand caudalrami are not setulose, and the endopods of legs 2 and 3 are only 2-segmented. Marked differences between 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FACFF858FA46F871" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1290,1411,1942,1968]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fijiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FACFF858FADBF86E" box="[1290,1310,1942,1967]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FAE9F858FA46F871" box="[1324,1411,1942,1968]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FA4FF858FC9EF813" bold="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FA4FF858FC9EF813" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FC4BF876FBD6F813" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[910,1043,1976,2002]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gryphina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC4BF876FC67F810" box="[910,930,1976,2001]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FC6BF876FBD6F813" box="[942,1043,1976,2002]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">gryphina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FBDCF876FBB5F813" bold="true" box="[1049,1136,1976,2002]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FBDCF876FBB5F813" box="[1049,1136,1976,2002]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
include the distal endopodal segments of legs 2 and 4 which are armed with 4 and 1 setae, respectively, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB53BD1FBEDF832FB61F7D7" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[1064,1188,2044,2070]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fijiensis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FBEDF832FB61F7D7" box="[1064,1188,2044,2070]" italics="true" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">D. fijiensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB53BD1FB6BF832FACFF7D7" bold="true" box="[1198,1290,2044,2070]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB53BD1FB6BF832FACFF7D7" box="[1198,1290,2044,2070]" pageId="484" pageNumber="485" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(comparedto 5 and 0 setae, respectively, in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB43BD0FE1BFF60FDA3FF06" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" box="[478,614,173,199]" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gryphina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FE1BFF60FE37FF06" box="[478,498,174,199]" italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FDC4FF63FDA3FF06" box="[513,614,173,199]" italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">gryphina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FDABFF63FD0CFF06" bold="true" box="[622,713,173,199]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB43BD0FDABFF63FD0CFF06" box="[622,713,173,199]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
), and the medial and outermost setae on the mandibular exopod are 0.6 times as long as the 3 middle setae whereas in 
<taxonomicName id="4C6D4D5EEEB43BD0FD2BFF3CFF28FEEC" authority="Kim &amp; Boxshall, 2020" authorityName="Kim &amp; Boxshall" authorityYear="2020" class="Maxillopoda" family="Notodelphyidae" genus="Doroixys" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyclopoida" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gryphina" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FD2BFF3CFCC7FECA" box="[750,770,242,267]" italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">D</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FF4DFEDDFF28FEEC" box="[136,237,275,301]" italics="true" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">gryphina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B919EACFEEB43BD0FF3DFEDDFE93FEEC" bold="true" box="[248,342,275,301]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A22A57B4EEB43BD0FF3DFEDDFE93FEEC" box="[248,342,275,301]" pageId="485" pageNumber="486" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
the medial seta is not shorter than 3 middle setae and the outermost seta is about half as long as the other 4 setae.
